name: works_list
description:
Function Name is works_list. Description:Returns a list of work items matching the request [argument name - applies_to_part, description = Filters for work belonging to any of the provided parts][argument name - created_by, description = Filters for work created by any of these users][argument name - issue.priority, description = Filters for issues with any of the provided priorities. Allowed values: p0, p1, p2, p3][argument name - issue.rev_orgs, description = Filters for issues with any of the provided Rev organizations][argument name - limit, description = The maximum number of works to return. The default is '50'][argument name - owned_by, description = Filters for work owned by any of these users][argument name - stage.name, description = Filters for records in the provided stage(s) by name][argument name - ticket.needs_response, description = Filters for tickets that need a response][argument name - ticket.rev_org, description = Filters for tickets associated with any of the provided Rev organizations][argument name - ticket.severity, description = Filters for tickets with any of the provided severities. Allowed values: blocker, high, low, medium][argument name - ticket.source_channel, description = Filters for tickets with any of the provided source ch ][argument name - types, description = Filters for work of the provided types. Allowed values: issue, ticket, task]Examples - query1: List all work items related to the 'Production' part, created by user 'John Doe', and with the priority 'p1'.
query2: Retrieve work items related to both 'Design' and 'Development' parts, owned by user 'Alice', and with a severity of 'high'.
query3: Get a list of tickets that need a response, associated with 'RevOrg1' and have the source channels 'Email' or 'Chat'.
query4: List the first 20 task items in the 'Testing' stage.
query5: Retrieve all issue type work items related to the 'Research' part and belonging to 'RevOrg2'.

name: summarize_objects
description:
Function Name is summarize_objects. Description:Summarizes a list of objects. The logic of how to summarize a particular object type is an internal implementation detail. [argument name - objects, description = List of objects to summarize]Examples - query1: Summarize a list of customer reviews and provide an overall summary of their sentiment.
query2: Summarize a list of articles on a given topic and provide a concise summary of each article.
query3: Summarize a list of financial reports and provide an overview of the key insights.
query4: Summarize a list of product specifications and generate a comprehensive summary of their features.
query5: Summarize a list of employee performance evaluations and generate a summary report highlighting areas of improvement.

name: prioritize_objects
description:
Function Name is prioritize_objects. Description:Returns a list of objects sorted by priority. The logic of what constitutes priority for a given object is an internal implementation detail. [argument name - objects, description = A list of objects to be prioritized]Examples - query1: Given a list of tasks T, prioritize the objects based on urgency.
query2: Given a list of customer issues I, sort the objects by priority.
query3: Can you show me an example of how to use prioritize_objects function with a list of bugs?
query4: How does the prioritize_objects function handle objects with the same priority level?
query5: I need to prioritize a list of features F, can you help me with the prioritize_objects function?

name: add_work_items_to_sprint
description:
Function Name is add_work_items_to_sprint. Description:Adds the given work items to the sprint [argument name - work_ids, description = A list of work item IDs to be added to the sprint.][argument name - sprint_id, description = The ID of the sprint to which the work items should be added]Examples - query1: Add work items with IDs [123, 124, 125] to sprint with ID 456.
query2: Can you add work items 789 and 790 to the sprint with ID 567?
query3: I need to add work items 111, 222, and 333 to sprint 789. Can you help with that?
query4: Please add work item 456 to sprint 654.
query5: How can I add work items 777 and 888 to the sprint with ID 999?

name: get_sprint_id
description:
Function Name is get_sprint_id. Description:Returns the ID of the current sprint Examples - query1: What is the ID of the current sprint?
query2: Display the ID of the active sprint.
query3: How can I retrieve the ID of the current sprint?
query4: Show me the current sprint's ID.
query5: Get the ID of the ongoing sprint.

name: get_similar_work_items
description:
Function Name is get_similar_work_items. Description:Returns a list of work items that are similar to the given work item [argument name - work_id, description = The ID of the work item for which you want to find similar items]Examples - query1: Get work items similar to work item W23.
query2: Find work items similar to the task assigned to John.
query3: List work items similar to the bug reported in Issue #1234.
query4: Show me work items similar to the feature request with ID F567.
query5: Provide a list of work items similar to the user story in sprint 5.

name: search_object_by_name
description:
Function Name is search_object_by_name. Description:Given a search string, returns the id of a matching object in the system of record. If multiple matches are found, it returns the one where the confidence is highest. [argument name - query, description = The search string, could be for example customer’s name, part name, user name.]Examples - query1: Find the object id for customer "John Smith".
query2: Search for the object id of the part "XWZ123".
query3: Get the id of the user "Jane Doe" in the system.
query4: Look up the object id for the customer "ACME Corp".
query5: Retrieve the object id for the user "James Brown".

name: create_actionable_tasks_from_text
description:
Function Name is create_actionable_tasks_from_text. Description:Given a text, extracts actionable insights, and creates tasks for them, which are kind of a work item. [argument name - text, description = The text from which the actionable insights need to be created.]Examples - Query 1: Given the project status report, create actionable tasks for the identified risks and issues.
Query 2: Extract actionable insights from the marketing campaign analysis report and generate tasks for improvement.
Query 3: From the customer feedback survey results, create tasks for addressing the highlighted areas for improvement.
Query 4: Create actionable tasks based on the sales team meeting minutes to follow up on potential leads and client concerns.
Query 5: Generate tasks from the performance review feedback to address skill development and performance improvement areas.

name: who_am_i
description:
Function Name is who_am_i. Description:Returns the ID of the current user Examples - query1: Display my user ID. 
query2: Retrieve current user's ID. 
query3: Show who am I.
query4: Get my user ID.
query5: What is my user ID?
